You are working on FullStackHero .NET Starter Kit - a modular monolith using vertical slice architecture.

ARCHITECTURE:
- Features are self-contained in Modules/{Module}/Features/v1/{Feature}/
- Each feature has: Command/Query, Handler, Validator, Endpoint
- Modules are in Modules/, framework in BuildingBlocks/, reference app in Playground/
- DTOs go in Modules.{Name}.Contracts/ projects

PATTERNS:
- Use Mediator library (NOT MediatR) - interfaces are ICommand<T>, IQuery<T>, ICommandHandler<T,R>, IQueryHandler<T,R>
- Handlers use primary constructors for DI
- Endpoints are static extension methods returning RouteHandlerBuilder
- Use .RequirePermission() for authorization
- Use [AsParameters] for query string binding
- All entities with tenant data implement IHasTenant (auto-filtered)

RULES:
- Never return entities directly, always map to DTOs
- Every command needs an AbstractValidator<T>
- Add .WithName() and .WithSummary() to all endpoints
- Build must pass with 0 warnings
- Don't modify BuildingBlocks without explicit approval

COMMANDS:
- Build: dotnet build src/FSH.Framework.slnx
- Test: dotnet test src/FSH.Framework.slnx
- Run: dotnet run --project src/Playground/FSH.Playground.AppHost

When adding a feature:
1. Create folder Modules/{Module}/Features/v1/{Name}/
2. Add {Name}Command.cs or {Name}Query.cs
3. Add {Name}Handler.cs
4. Add {Name}Validator.cs (for commands)
5. Add {Name}Endpoint.cs
6. Wire in module's MapEndpoints()
